{% # Validation - Block - Spacer v2.0.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.0.0 — token-section is now the real production theme-root grid (drop the `display: block` override + the `.block-validation-suite` flex wrapper). Spacers render as direct children of the grid, so the rhythm-neutral substrate rule applies and is assertable (a spacer + the block after it take no rhythm margin). Harness chrome + the outline/label indicator move to `validation--harness-styles`. Template matrix rewritten for spacer v2.0.0 (single `size` picker backed by the `spacing` metaobject, baked by handle; the old px `breakpoint`/`spacer_block_size` settings are gone). Per `validation.md` § Harness layout.
  - v1.0.0 — initial

  Block-validation harness for `spacer`. The JSON template at
  `templates/index.validation--primitive--spacer.json` bakes the test
  matrix as block instances; the section renders them directly as children
  of the theme-root grid, labelled via `validation--block-labels`.

  Diagnostic intent:
  1. Each `size` token resolves to its spacing height; resize across 768px
     to validate the token's own mobile/desktop divide.
  2. `background_color` turns the spacer into a colored band.
  3. Spacer is rhythm-neutral — it takes no --block-rhythm margin even
     though the section sets one. The dashed outline shows each spacer's
     bounds even when transparent / 0-height.

  Per-page exception: spacers are rhythm-neutral (margin-block-start forced
  to 0), so as direct grid children they would butt together with no gap.
  A harness-only `margin-block-end` separates the cases for legibility — it
  touches neither the measured `block-size` (the spacer's height) nor
  `margin-block-start` (the rhythm-neutral property under test).

  Reachable only at /?view=validation--primitive--spacer.
  See `.context/docs/validation.md`.
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign max_inline_size = section.settings.max_inline_size
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root">
  {% render 'validation--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class="validation__intro">
    <h1>Block: spacer</h1>
    <p>
      Matrix in
      <code>templates/index.validation--primitive--spacer.json</code>. Each entry is one block instance — a
      <code>size</code> token (baked by handle), with or without a <code>background_color</code> band. Resize across
      768px to validate the token's mobile/desktop divide. The dashed outline shows each spacer's bounds even when
      transparent or 0-height; spacers are rhythm-neutral, so the visible gap between cases is a harness affordance, not
      block rhythm.
    </p>
  </header>

  {% if section.blocks.size > 0 %}
    {% content_for 'blocks' %}

    {% render 'validation--block-labels', section: section %}
  {% else %}
    <p class="validation__empty">No blocks declared in the template.</p>
  {% endif %}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  {% if max_inline_size and max_inline_size != blank %}
    --max-inline-size: {{ max_inline_size }}px;
  {% endif %}
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
{% render 'validation--harness-styles' %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Block: spacer",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--validation--primitive--spacer",
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@theme" }],
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "max_inline_size",
      "label": "Max width",
      "min": 800,
      "max": 1920,
      "step": 20,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 1280
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

{% stylesheet %}
  @layer components {
    /* Per-page exception: separate the rhythm-neutral spacers for legibility.
       margin-block-end is harness-only — it leaves block-size (height under
       test) and margin-block-start (rhythm-neutral, under test) untouched. */
    .shopify-section--validation--primitive--spacer {
      token-section > .shopify-block--spacer {
        margin-block-end: 2.5rem;
      }
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}
